\"#feedbackModal_main_2532570\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 19, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104txe1665702762645.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/txe1665702762645.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/txe1665702762645.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"txe1665702762645\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n               \n Microsoft IIS and Uniface\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">You can use a Microsoft Internet Information Services (IIS) web server to deploy Uniface web applications. Although IIS is a web server, it does not have a servlet engine that can execute servlets such as the Uniface Web Request Dispatcher (WRD) and SOAP Request Dispatcher (SRD), or Java server pages.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"txe1665702762645__p_d23576e1_d23577e1_d23578e1\">Instead, it can direct requests to the Tomcat servlet engine using the Apache ISAPI Redirector (<span class=\"ph filepath\">isapi_redirector.dll</span>, also known as the IIS connector). The IIS connector communicates with Tomcat via an AJP (Apache JServ Protocol) connector.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"txe1665702762645__p_d23579e1_d23580e1_d23581e1\">The ISAPI Redirector and default configuration files are provided with the Tomcat installation. The redirector needs to be correctly configured before you can use IIS for your Uniface web applications.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"txe1665702762645__p_d23582e1_d23583e1_d23584e1\">If you have already installed IIS and are installing the\n      Uniface Enterprise Edition 10.4.02, or earlier, you can have the Uniface installer perform\n      this configuration for you. (Choose <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Advanced installation</span> and select\n        <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Configure IIS for use with Uniface</span>.) The Uniface Enterprise Edition\n      10.4.03, and later, installer no longer comes with the possibility to configure IIS during\n      installation. You will need to manually configure IIS. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ceb1665702762718.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ceb1665702762718.html\" title=\"You can use a Microsoft Internet Information Services (IIS) web server to deploy Uniface web applications. However, because IIS cannot execute servlets such as the Uniface WRD and SRD, it must redirect client requests to the Tomcat servlet engine. To do so it uses the Apache ISAPI Redirector, also known as the IIS connector.\">Configuring Microsoft IIS to Use Tomcat</a>.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"txe1665702762645__note_w1241ab1b5b7_w1242ab1b5_w1243ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> This configuration fails if IIS is not installed, or if it has been previously configured to run the servlets provided with Uniface products.</div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"txe1665702762645__p_d23585e1_d23586e1_d23587e1\">If configuration is unsuccessful, or if you are using a Tomcat installation that is not the one delivered with Uniface, you will need to manually configure IIS. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ceb1665702762718.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ceb1665702762718.html\" title=\"You can use a Microsoft Internet Information Services (IIS) web server to deploy Uniface web applications. However, because IIS cannot execute servlets such as the Uniface WRD and SRD, it must redirect client requests to the Tomcat servlet engine. To do so it uses the Apache ISAPI Redirector, also known as the IIS connector.\">Configuring Microsoft IIS to Use Tomcat</a>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"txe1665702762645__p_d23588e1_d23589e1_d23590e1\">The default configuration provided by Uniface is\n      unsecured, so even if it is successful, we recommend modifying the configuration to protect\n      the communication channel between IIS and Tomcat. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"azt1670589847072.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/azt1670589847072.html\" title=\"If you are using Microsoft IIS as your web server with Tomcat as the servlet engine, it is recommended that you protect the connection with a secret string. To update your configuration, you need to edit the Tomcat server.xml file and the workers.properties file, both located in /common/tomcat/conf/ of your Uniface installation directory.\">Configure Security for the ISAPI Redirector</a>. </p>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532570\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532570\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Microsoft IIS and Uniface Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 19, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Microsoft IIS and Uniface You can use a Microsoft Internet Information Services (IIS) web server to deploy Uniface web applications. Although IIS is a web server, it does not have a servlet engine that can execute servlets such as the Uniface Web Request Dispatcher (WRD) and SOAP Request Dispatcher (SRD), or Java server pages. Instead, it can direct requests to the Tomcat servlet engine using the Apache ISAPI Redirector ( isapi_redirector.dll , also known as the IIS connector). The IIS connector communicates with Tomcat via an AJP (Apache JServ Protocol) connector. The ISAPI Redirector and default configuration files are provided with the Tomcat installation. The redirector needs to be correctly configured before you can use IIS for your Uniface web applications. If you have already installed IIS and are installing the Uniface Enterprise Edition 10.4.02, or earlier, you can have the Uniface installer perform this configuration for you. (Choose Advanced installation and select Configure IIS for use with Uniface .) The Uniface Enterprise Edition 10.4.03, and later, installer no longer comes with the possibility to configure IIS during installation. You will need to manually configure IIS. For more information, see Configuring Microsoft IIS to Use Tomcat . Note: This configuration fails if IIS is not installed, or if it has been previously configured to run the servlets provided with Uniface products. If configuration is unsuccessful, or if you are using a Tomcat installation that is not the one delivered with Uniface, you will need to manually configure IIS. For more information, see Configuring Microsoft IIS to Use Tomcat . The default configuration provided by Uniface is unsecured, so even if it is successful, we recommend modifying the configuration to protect the communication channel between IIS and Tomcat. For more information, see Configure Security for the ISAPI Redirector . Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}